# docker

To get started, run `coder templates init`. When prompted, select this template.
Follow the on-screen instructions to proceed.

## Adding/removing images

Edit the template to make a new image available to users:

```sh
# Open the template
vim main.tf
```

Modify your file to match the following:

```diff
variable "docker_image" {
  default = "latest-gpu-jypyter"
  description = "Docker tag to use for the tensorflow/tensorflow image"

  validation {
-    condition = contains(["latest-gpu-jypyter"])
+    condition = contains(["latest-gpu-jypyter", "2.8.2-gpu-jypyter"])
    error_message = "Not a valid tage. Please check https://hub.docker.com/r/${var.docker_image}/tags"
  }
  sensitive = true
}
```

Update the template:

```sh
coder template update tensorflow
```

You can also remove images from the validation list. Workspaces using older template versions will continue using the removed image until you update the workspace to the latest version.

## Extending this template

See the [kreuzwerker/docker](https://registry.terraform.io/providers/kreuzwerker/docker) Terraform provider documentation to
add the following features to your Coder template:

- SSH/TCP docker host
- Registry authentication
- Build args
- Volume mounts
- Custom container spec
- More

We also welcome contributions!
